<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="308" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d308">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Palma</persName> to
                                President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-04"><hi rend="italic">September 4,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I profoundly deplore the accident that has befallen Your Excellency and
                            make sincere wishes for the complete restoration of your health.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">T. Estrada
                            Palma</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>